## <a id='overview'></a>Overview

Azuqua Platform Connector for Pivotal Cloud Foundry (PCF) lets PCF developers connect their apps to the [Azuqua](https://azuqua.com) service, which orchestrates connections to databases, API-based microservices, and commercial cloud applications like Salesforce, Oracle, Marketo, JIRA, and 60+ other business tools. Azuqua is a scalable, customizable, and secure way to trigger workflows and synchronize data across the enterprise.

Azuqua Platform Connector for PCF includes the following key features:

* **Prebuilt Connections**: Library of 60+ commercial cloud applications for CRM, marketing automation, project management, communications, etc.

* **Custom API Integration**: Connect to any custom-built API.

* **Scheduled FLOs**: Create [FLO](https://learn.azuqua.com/read/02-flo-structure) workflows that run on a periodic schedule. Great for weekly data syncs for reporting, hourly systems checks, quarterly reviews, etc.

* **List Processing**: Take actions for each record in a list. The list might include all stakeholders on a project that need to be notified when a task is completed, or a list of customers that need to be segmented for a specific email.

* **File Handling**: Azuqua can automatically append, migrate, update, and extract files in any SaaS application that can receive it, like a Salesforce documents library or a JIRA project. It can also synchronize files with file management tools like Box, Dropbox, and Egnyte.

