## <a id='broker'></a>Azuqua Platform Connector Service Broker and Tile

The Azuqua Platform Connector service broker is a Java app that deploys to PCF and connects applications to the Azuqua Platform Connector service, via one or more Azuqua accounts. The broker component lets developers easily bind their apps to the service using either Pivotal Apps Manager or the command line. The service broker also publishes Azuqua Platform Connector service plans to the Pivotal Marketplace.

In the PCF Installation Dashboard, the Azuqua Platform Connector tile installs the Azuqua Platform Connector broker and registers it with Cloud Foundry. The tile enables installation, configuration, and subsequent use of Azuqua Platform Connector with your PCF apps.

Customers interested in using Azuqua Platform Connector can obtain a free Developer license [here](https://azuqua.com/integrate/pivotal-cloud-foundry/). 

## <a id="reqs"></a>Requirements

To use Azuqua Platform Connector for PCF, you need the following:

* An Azuqua account (Public Cloud) with an Organization to design workflows. You can create your own account or an administrator can create one for you. For more information about managing users in an existing Azuqua Organization, refer to [Manage Organizations](http://help.azuqua.com/help/manage-organizations).

* A PCF installation with Elastic Runtime configured with User Account and Authentication (UAA), the internal user store.

* PCF Stemcell version 3146 ubuntu-trusty.

* SSL certificates in your UAA that validate successfully in the stemcell you deploy the Azuqua Platform Connector tile on.

* Network permissions for ingress from and egress to Azuqua in any PCF space where Azuqua Platform Connector service instances deploy, and for any users workstations.

## <a id="limitations"></a>Limitations

The v0.9 Azuqua Platform Connector PCF tile is limited to providing Single Sign-On to a single Azuqua user. All PCF users with UAA permissions to the deployed service will authenticate to Azuqua as the configured user.

